## 2. Technical Baseline Deficiencies (Sourced Gaps)
*   **Local Password & Account Lockout Policies:**
    - *Finding:* [e.g., Password length set to default 7 characters; no lockout policy active]
    - *Reference Source:* According to **Microsoft Docs ("Password Policy GPO Best Practices")**, passwords must be a minimum of 12 characters, and accounts must lock out after a maximum of 10 failed login attempts.
*   **Endpoint Disk Encryption:**
    - *Finding:* [e.g., BitLocker is disabled on remote laptop workstations]
    - *Reference Source:* According to **Microsoft Docs ("BitLocker GPO Reference")**, full disk encryption using XTS-AES 256-bit parameters must be enforced via Active Directory or Intune MDM.
*   **Perimeter Log Routing:**
    - *Finding:* [e.g., Local firewall logs are not being forwarded to a centralized security repository]
    - *Reference Source:* Per **Fortinet Knowledge Base (FD-43759)**, configure syslog forwarding on all edge appliances to send audited sessions to a secure, centralized server.

